Description:
Company Profile
Minto Explorations Ltd is a Yukon based mining company that operates the Minto copper, gold mine. It is located 240 kilometres north along the Klondike Highway from the capital Whitehorse.
Minto is looking to build its work force and is looking for a range of candidates who would like to become part of a dynamic, team-oriented, and performance-driven environment.
Position
We are seeking a
Sr. Mine Engineer
for a full time/regular position. The role will be based at the Minto mine, which is a camp-based operation with a two week on/two week off rotation.
The Ideal Candidate
You will have;
5-7 years related experience as an Engineer;
Hold a P. Eng designation;
Experience working in a remote mining environment;
Must be eligible to work in Canada;
Ability to develop and foster strong working relationships;
Ability to work with a diverse cross-cultural workforce;
Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities;
Valid driver's license;
Physically fit to perform the duties of the position.
Responsibilities
Provide mine engineering expertise during the feasibility and construction phases of the underground operations to ensure operational needs and standards are met;
Support and monitors the implementation of long-term mine plans and short-term detailed mine execution plans, provides the necessary production parameters needed to ensure achievement of the long-term mine plan;
Provides support in the engineering of such ventilation, rock mechanics/ground control, infrastructure designs, economic studies, mining sequence establishment, survey, and drill and blast design;
Optimizes the extraction of mineral deposits to meet Company objectives;
Provides advice and direction to mining operations in developing and implementing engineering, mine design, planning and scheduling strategies;
Mentor junior engineers within the team as necessary;
Support Key Performance Indicators (KPI’s) with recommendations to improve with changes in standard operating procedures;
Maintain Mine Site quality control processes and procedures;
Understand all key aspects of production targets;
Practice and actively promote company environmental, health, safety and operational policies and procedures;
Ensure that safety issues are reported and promptly remedied;
Demonstrate safety leadership within a team environment and promote environmental awareness in all work or task related duties;
Maintain a high standard of performance in your duties;
Participate in site specific training;
Comply with company standards, as well as Yukon Territory and Canadian federal standards;
Other duties may be assigned from time to time as required by the Company.
Job Types: Full-time, Fly-In/Fly-Out, Permanent
Schedule:
12 hour shift
Education:
Bachelor's Degree (preferred)
Experience:
Engineering: 5 years (preferred)
Licence/Certification:
P. Eng Designation (preferred)
Work remotely:
No
